nodes.bodyText:
AtomicReference<Optional<CompletableFuture<NettyPartitionRequestClient>>> is a bit complicated type and it's not that easy to understand how is it working. Why not using something simpler and more precisely expressing the intention, that the first caller completes the future?:
AtomicBoolean isFirstOne = new AtomicBoolean(false);
CompletableFuture<NettyPartitionRequestClient> clientFuture = clients.computeIfAbsent(connectionId, unused -> {
	CompletableFuture<NettyPartitionRequestClient> future = new CompletableFuture<>();
	isFirstOne.set(true);
	return future;
});
if (isFirstOne.get()) {
	clientFuture.complete(connectWithRetries(connectionId)));
}

